data.description: Welcome home to Charleston Park, a community located in one of the most desirable school districts in the state DD2. This beautifully maintained homes has great curb appeal and a small yard that makes maintenance very simple. Upon entering the home  you will notice the home has been meticulously maintained and has a very functional space that is accented with neutral colors and fosters all sorts of activities.  The home has laminate flooring throughout the first level, while carpet and LVP adorne the second floor. The large living room joins the separate kitchen and dining areas. A large cut out connects the two, so the entirebottom floor feels as though it were one large room. The kitchen is handsomely appointed with quartz countertops, an island, and plenty of cabinet storage. A half bath is located just down the hall, as well as additional storage.   Upstairs you will find the master bedroom, two good-sized bedrooms, and a secondary bath with oversized vanity and polished cultured marble countertops. The bathrooms have had the flooring upgraded to LVP to provide a stylish and durable flooring that your family will enjoy for years without worry. The Master bedroom is spacious and has with a tray ceiling for added luxury. The master bathroom has a vanity space, polished cultured marble countertops, and a separate tub and shower. This room has also been redone with LVP to add a durable stylish appeal. There is a large walk in closet as well.   The backyard features full privacy fenced and a deck for enjoying the outside air.   This home is centrally located to military bases, retail shopping, multiple highways, award winning schools, historic downtown Charleston and much more.
